  "prompt": "What are your favourite Bob Dylan lyrics?",
  "response": "Bob Dylan has written many iconic lyrics that resonate with listeners on various levels. Some of my favorites include:\n\n1. **\u201cThe Times They Are a-Changin'\u201d** - The lyrics speak to the inevitability of change and the need for people to adapt and embrace new ideas.\n\n2. **\u201cBlowin' in the Wind\u201d** - This song poses profound questions about peace, freedom, and justice, making it a timeless anthem for social change.\n\n3. **\u201cLike a Rolling Stone\u201d** - The imagery and emotional depth in this song depict a powerful narrative of loss and self-discovery.\n\n4. **\u201cTangled Up in Blue\u201d** - The nonlinear storytelling and vivid characters create a poignant exploration of love and memory.\n\n5. **\"All Along the Watchtower\"** - This song's surreal and almost apocalyptic imagery has intrigued listeners and inspired countless interpretations.\n\nDylan's ability to weave intricate stories and profound truths into his lyrics is unparalleled, making his music timeless and impactful. Do you have any favorite lyrics of his?",
